Example 3: a method that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element from the original array, starting with the first element. For instance:
every_other([1,4,7,2,5]) # => [1,7,5]

# Informal Pseudo-Code

Iterate through each element of an array.
Return the value of the element for arrays at space 0 and even spaces only. 
Print the return value. 

# Formal Pseudo-Code

START

SET new_array = empty array

iterator = 0

WHILE iterator < length of the array
  RETURN array at space "iterator"
  iterator = iterator + 1

END
